dly sit on giant thrones in the clouds). &#10;Seems to me that none of the Abrahamic fairy tales have much of a place in places of education (unless one is involved in a higher education religious and cultural studies class). &#10;Now that we have purged our schools of the Lord's Prayer, singing God Save the Queen and all other vestiges of our Judeo-Christian heritage, it seems totally wrong headed to encourage Islamic prayer rooms - that's what mosques are for. &#10;Perhaps if the mosques want to give some tit for tat, they would allow their members to engage in agnostic thought study groups. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="878" language="en" documentId="1226" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="RalphineJohnstone" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/tempers-flare-over-prayer-in-schools-1.1104775" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1226" notes="" title="Tempers flare over prayer in schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="83"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="84" end="123"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="124" end="330"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="331" end="511"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="512" end="748"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="749" end="878"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59"/></xmi:XMI>